<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870626-0044 </DOCNO><HL> International Corporate Report:Argyll Says Pre-Tax ProfitRose 25% in the Fiscal Year</HL><DD> 06/26/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> EARNINGS (ERN)FOOD andamp; BEVERAGE, HOUSEHOLD GOODS, SUPERMARKETS, TOBACCO (FAB) </IN><TEXT>   ARGYLL GROUP PLC said pre-tax profit in the year ended March 28 climbed 25%, to #80.6 million ($130.9 million) from #64.6 million the year before. Sales rose 12%, to #2.13 billion ($3.46 billion) from #1.91 billion.    The British food retailer also said it plans a one-for-eight rights issue to raise #208.4 million to finance its &quot;substantial&quot; development program for its Safeway stores in Britain.    An extraordinary charge of #3.2 million related to business and stock disposals reduced net income to #50.6 million. The year before, and extraordinary loss of #34.2 million related to its unsuccessful bid for Distillers Co. brought earnings to #10.8 million. </TEXT></DOC>